 chief executives in the media industry]]\n[[Category:American libertarians]]\n[[Category:American mass media owners]]\n[[Category:American media company founders]]\n[[Category:American newspaper chain founders]]\n[[Category:American newspaper publishers (people)]]\n[[Category:American people of English descent]]\n[[Category:American people of Irish descent]]\n[[Category:American people of Scottish descent]]\n[[Category:American victims of crime]]\n[[Category:Australian billionaires]]\n[[Category:Australian chairmen of corporations]]\n[[Category:Australian chief executives]]\n[[Category:Australian emigrants to the United States]]\n[[Category:Australian expatriates in the United Kingdom]]\n[[Category:Australian libertarians]]\n[[Category:Australian media company founders]]\n[[Category:Australian newspaper chain founders]]\n[[Category:Australian people of English descent]]\n[[Category:Australian people of Irish descent]]\n[[Category:Australian people of Scottish descent]]\n[[Category:Australian republicans]]\n[[Category:Australian victims of crime]]\n[[Category:Businesspeople from Los Angeles]]\n[[Category:Businesspeople from Melbourne]]\n[[Category:Christian libertarians]]\n[[Category:Companions of the Order of Australia]]\n[[Category:Critics of the European Union]]\n[[Category:Fox Broadcasting Company executives]]\n[[Category:Knights Commander of the Order of St Gregory the Great]]\n[[Category:Los Angeles Dodgers owners]]\n[[Category:Murdoch family|Rupert]]\n[[Category:New York Post people]]\n[[Category:News Corporation people]]\n[[Category:People associated with the News International phone hacking scandal]]\n[[Category:People educated at Geelong Grammar School]]\n[[Category:People from Adelaide]]\n[[Category:People from Beverly Hills, California]]\n[[Category:People from Centre Island, New York]]\n[[Category:People with acquired American citizenship]]\n[[Category:Manhattan Institute for Policy Research]]\n[[Category:20th-century Australian businesspeople]]\n[[Category:Australian newspaper proprietors]]\n", "name_user": "49.179.28.170", "label": "unsafe", "comment": "(Funny)", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Rupert_Murdoch"}
{"title_page": "Dilawar Cheema", "text_new": "{{Infobox settlement\n| official_name           = Dilawar Cheema\n| name                    = \n| settlement_type         = [[Village]]\n| image_skyline           =\n| imagesize               = 240px\n| image_alt               = \n| image_caption           = \n| image_map               = \n| mapsize                 = 100px\n| map_alt                 = \n| map_caption             = \n| coordinates             = {{coord|32.3360336|73.9379454|region:PK_type:city|display=inline,title}}\n| pushpin_map             = Pakistan\n| pushpin_label_position  = <!-- left, right, top, bottom, none -->\n| pushpin_map_alt         = \n| pushpin_mapsize         = \n| pushpin_map_caption     =  \n| subdivision_type        = [[Country]]\n| subdivision_name        = [[Pakistan]]\n| subdivision_type1       = [[Subdivisions of Pakistan|Province]]\n| subdivision_name1       = [[Punjab (Pakistan)|Punjab]]\n| subdivision_type2       = [[Districts of Pakistan|District]]\n| subdivision_name2       = [[Gujranwala District|Gujranwala]]\n| population_total        = \n| population_as_of        = \n| population_est          = 7373 <ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.pbs.gov.pk/sites/default/files/bwpsr/punjab/GUJRANWALA_BLOCKWISE.pdf#page=93 |title=GUJRANWALA BLOCKWISE |publisher=[[Pakistan Bureau of Statistics]] |access-date=2020-04-04}}</ref>\n| pop_est_as_of           = 2017\n| population_footnotes    = \n| area_total_km2          = 2.41\n| elevation_m             = \n| elevation_m_min         = \n| elevation_m_max         = \n| population_density_km2  = \n| leader_title            = \n| leader_name             = \n| leader_title1           = \n| leader_name1            = \n| area_code               = 055\n| area_code_type          = [[List of dialling codes of Pakistan|Calling code]]\n| timezone1               = [[Pakistan Standard Time|PST]]\n| utc_offset1             = +5\n| website                 = \n| footnotes               = \n}}\n'''Dilawar Cheema''' ([[Punjabi]], {{lang-ur|{{Nastaliq|  \u062f\u0644\u0627\u0648\u0631 \u0686\u064a\u0645\u0647}}}}) is a Village in Tehsil [[Wazirabad]], [[Gujranwala District]], [[Punjab, Pakistan]].<ref>[http://www.nrb.gov.pk/lg_election/union.asp?district=9&dn=Gujranwala. Towns & Unions in the City District of Gujranwala] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120428182843/http://www.nrb.gov.pk/lg_election/union.asp?district=9&dn=Gujranwala. |date=2012-04-28 }} National Reconstruction Bureau, Pakistan. Retrieved May 11, 2011</ref> It is located in a central area between [[Alipur Chatha]], [[Wazirabad]] and [[Gujranwala]].<ref>[http://www.fallingrain.com/world/PK/04/Dilawar_Chima.html Location of Dilawar Cheema] fallingrain.com. Falling Rain Genomics. Retrieved May 11, 2011</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.bolnews.com/pakistan/2019/10/military-training-aircraft-crashes-in-wazirabad/|title=Military training aircraft crashes in Wazirabad|date=2019-10-19|website=BOL News|language=en-US|access-date=2020-04-04}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.dawn.com/news/1511748|title=Pilots safe as Pak Army trainer aircraft crash-lands near Wazirabad|last=Mirza|first=Iqbal|date=2019-10-19|website=DAWN.COM|language=en|access-date=2020-04-04}}</ref> It is also one of the well known Union Councils in [[Gujranwala District]]. The only way to get to Dilawar Cheema is by Road. Dilawar Cheema is direcly connected with Dilawar Cheema Khurd, Dera Chungran, Bara Pind, [[Kub Pora Cheema]] and Dharowal Kang, While connect with [[Ahmad Nagar Chattha]] via [[Kub Pora Cheema]] and [[Pathanke Cheema]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.thenews.com.pk/print/513608-construction-of-five-roads-begins|title=Construction of five roads begins|website=www.thenews.com.pk|language=en|access-date=2020-04-04}}</ref> 80% population in the village is [[Muslim]], the remaining 20% is Non-Muslim. For finance management a [[Habib Bank Limited]] - HBL Dilawar Cheema Branch is functional in the village.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://branches.pk/branch-detail/Habib-Bank-Limited-HBL-Dilawar-Cheema-Branch-Gujranwala|title=Habib Bank Limited - HBL Dilawar Cheema Branch Gujranwala - Phone Number, Branch Code & Address|website=branches.pk|access-date=2020-04-04}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://bisegrw.edu.pk/authorized-banks.html|title=Board of Intermediate and Secondary Education, Gujranwala|website=bisegrw.edu.pk|access-date=2020-04-04}}</ref><ref>{{Cite book|url=https://books.google.com.pk/books?id=B1ccAQAAMAAJ&q=Dilawar+cheema&dq=Dilawar+cheema&hl=en&sa=X&ved=0ahUKEwiB5bS-k87oAhWkuXEKHaO7Cm0Q6AEIOzAD|title=The Bank Directory|date=2007|publisher=Accuity|language=en}}</ref> Facility of Civil [[Veterinary hospital|Veterinary Hospital]] is also available.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://livestockpunjab.gov.pk/LiveStockAdmin/uploads/staff_images/aec5v.pdf#page=1|title=aec5v.pdf|last=|first=|date=|website=livestockpunjab.gov.pk|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-04-04}}</ref> \n\n== Education==\nGovernment Elementary School Dilawar Cheema,<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://tribune.com.pk/story/378051/school-education-poor-teacher-attendance-reported-at-34-gujranwala-schools/|title=School Education: Poor teacher attendance reported at 34 Gujranwala schools|last=Tribune.com.pk|date=2012-05-13|website=The Express Tribune|language=en|access-date=2020-04-04}}</ref> Government Girls and Boys Primary School<ref>{{Cite book|url=https://books.google.com.pk/books?id=J19zlT1BUw8C&q=Dilawar+cheema&dq=Dilawar+cheema&hl=en&sa=X&ved=0ahUKEwiB5bS-k87oAhWkuXEKHaO7Cm0Q6AEILTAB|title=Census of Primary Schools of the Punjab Province: Lahore Region, 1972-73|date=1973|publisher=Punjab Textbook Board|language=en}}</ref> and Government Girls and Boys High School (GGHS),<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.urdupoint.com/education/school/gujranwala/11807/gghs-dilawar-cheema.html|title=GGHS Dilawar Cheema Gujranwala - School Info & Teachers Profiles|website=UrduPoint|language=en|access-date=2020-04-04}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://hamariweb.com/directories/govt._girls_high_school_dilawar_cheema_edu87391.aspx|title=Govt. Girls High School Dilawar Cheema, Gujranwala|website=hamariweb.com|access-date=2020-04-04}}</ref> Dilawar Cheema are functional in the town by [[Government of Punjab, Pakistan]] under [[Board of Intermediate and Secondary Education, Gujranwala]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://open.punjab.gov.pk/schools/home/school_visit_detail/698849|title=Programme Monitoring & Implementation Unit|website=open.punjab.gov.pk|access-date=2020-04-04}}</ref> Punjab Governor [[Rafique Rajwana]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://nation.com.pk/08-Aug-2018/hasanabdal-gets-boys-degree-college|title=Hasanabdal gets boys\u2019 degree college|date=2018-08-08|website=The Nation|language=en|access-date=2020-04-04}}</ref> has formally approved Government Degree College for Women, Dilawar Cheema under the Annual Development Project,<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.dawn.com/news/1278265|title=New colleges approved for Gujranwala under ADP|last=Correspondent|first=The Newspaper's|date=2016-08-18|website=DAWN.COM|language=en|access-date=2020-04-04}}</ref> which is functional from 2019.<ref>{{Cite news|last=|first=|url=https://e.thenews.com.pk/pdf-data/gujranwala-part1-result-2019.pdf#page=28|title=GOVT. DEGREE COLLEGE FOR WOMEN, DILAWAR CHEEMA Part 1 Result 2019|date=|work=[[The News International]]|access-date=2020-04-04|url-status=live}}</ref> \n\n== See also ==\n* [[Pathanke Cheema]]\n* [[Jugna Chattha]]\n* [[Ghari Donger]]\n== References ==\n<references />\n\n{{Neighbourhoods of Gujranwala}}\n\n{{coord missing|Punjab, Pakistan}}\n\n[[Category:Populated places in Gujranwala District]]\n[[Category:Villages in Gujranwala District]]\n{{Gujranwala-geo-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox settlement\n| official_name           = Dilawar Cheema\n| name                    = \n| settlement_type         = [[Village]]\n| image_skyline           =\n| imagesize               = 240px\n| image_alt         